---
title: Pescado Veracruz with Olive Ragout, Burst Tomatoes, and Basmati Rice
description: Pescado Veracruz hails from the city of the same name, Veracruz, Mexico.  Founded by the Spanish, the city continues to be Mexico’s largest and busiest port. As a result, many European ingredients—such as olives—were introduced to Mexico via trade. This recipe is so satisfyingly simple to prepare—I never get tired of eating and making it.  –Chef Robert Stauning
